<TITLE> Two killed in Kushtia 'crossfire' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)Two more people were killed in so-called 'crossfire' during a clash with police in Kushtia early on Friday, police said. The death of the two raised the number of people killed in 'crossfire' in the south-western region to 31 in last three months. Superintendent of Kushtia police Shahabuddin Khan told bdnews24.com that Rokon, 32, and Samiruddin alias Hatkata Sagar, 34, were killed in a 'gunfight' with the police near Jagoti rail station under Sadar upazila. Khan said that a team of Detective Branch of police conducted an operation on a mango orchard near the railway station at 2:15am when the extremists opened fire and police retaliated in self-defence. The two were killed in the gunfight that ensued and their bodies were found after their associates fled the scene. Local people later identified the bodies. Officer-in-charge of Sadar Police Station AKM Faruk Hossain said the two killed were associated with the outlawed Purba Banglar Communist Party and there were 12 cases against Rokon, including five of murder charges, and 10 criminal cases against Sagar. Home minister Sahara Khatun on Nov 15 had claimed there were "no 'crossfire killings' since the current government took office." bdnews24.c
